==English==
===Etymology===
Russian [[перестройка]] (''perestroika''), restructuring.

===Noun===
'''perestroika'''

# [[Gorbachev]]'s [[reform]]s in the [[Soviet Union]] in the 1980s.
#*'''2004:''' [[w: Chris Wallace (journalist)|Chris Wallace]], ''Character:  Profiles in Presidential Courage''
#*:Gorbechev would introduce '''''glasnost''''' (openness and freedom) and ''perestroika'' (economic restructuring) to Russia under his tenure, ultimately freeing thousands of political prisoners and dissidents and trying to address the shortages in food and goods that had become the hallmarks of the failing Soviet economy.  

